cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.CC

This paper is about Selectional Preference (SP) acquisition, which is a natural language processing task. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also evaluates three representative SP acquisition methods, which involves machine learning and statistical modeling, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the potential of using SP to represent commonsense knowledge, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the Winograd Schema Challenge, which is a natural language understanding task, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the creation of a large-scale evaluation set, which could be relevant to cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
